---
const pageTitle = "Shadow Projection";
---

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
    <title>{pageTitle}</title>

    <style>
      :root {
        --paper: #ffffff;
        --ink: #000000;
        --line: #000000;
        --soft: #efefef;
        --blue: #0000ee;
        --red: #cc0000;
        --green: #008000;
      }

      html, body {
        margin: 0;
        padding: 0;
        background: var(--paper);
        color: var(--ink);
        font-family: "Times New Roman", Times, serif;
        font-size: 18px;
        line-height: 1.55;
      }

      a { text-decoration: underline; }
      a.blue { color: var(--blue); }
      a.red { color: var(--red); }
      a.green { color: var(--green); }

      .page {
        width: min(900px, calc(100% - 48px));
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 28px 0 60px;
      }

      .topbar {
        border: 1px solid var(--line);
        padding: 10px 14px;
        margin-bottom: 18px;
        text-align: center;
        background: #fafafa;
      }

      .topbar span {
        margin: 0 8px;
      }

      .frame {
        border: 1px solid var(--line);
        padding: 22px 24px 28px;
        position: relative;
        overflow: hidden;
        background:
          linear-gradient(to bottom, rgba(255,255,255,0.94), rgba(230,230,230,0.94)),
          repeating-linear-gradient(
            to bottom,
            rgba(0,0,0,0.03) 0px,
            rgba(0,0,0,0.03) 1px,
            transparent 1px,
            transparent 4px
          );
      }

      .symbol-bg {
        position: absolute;
        top: 50%;
        left: 50%;
        transform: translate(-50%, -50%) rotate(5deg);
        width: 300px;
        height: 300px;
        opacity: 0.18;
        z-index: 0;
      }

      .symbol-bg svg {
        width: 100%;
        height: 100%;
      }

      .content-layer {
        position: relative;
        z-index: 1;
      }

      h1 {
        font-size: 42px;
        text-align: center;
        margin: 0 0 8px;
      }

      .subtitle {
        text-align: center;
        font-size: 15px;
        margin-bottom: 24px;
      }

      .quote {
        margin: 22px auto;
        max-width: 680px;
        border: 1px solid var(--line);
        padding: 14px;
        background: linear-gradient(to bottom, #ececec, #e2e2e2);
        font-style: italic;
        text-align: center;
      }

      .section-title {
        font-size: 28px;
        text-align: center;
        margin: 30px 0 14px;
      }

      .mini-links {
        text-align: center;
        margin-top: 30px;
      }

      .mini-links a {
        margin: 0 10px;
      }

      .footer-note {
        text-align: center;
        margin-top: 26px;
        font-size: 14px;
      }
    </style>
  </head>

  <body>
    <div class="page">
      <div class="topbar">
        <span>[ <a class="blue" href="/">home</a> ]</span>
        <span>[ <a class="blue" href="/dreams">dreams index</a> ]</span>
        <span>[ <a class="green" href="/dreams/nightmares">previous</a> ]</span>
        <span>[ <a class="red" href="/dreams/active-imagination">next</a> ]</span>
      </div>

      <main class="frame">
        <div class="symbol-bg" aria-hidden="true">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 300 300" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
            <circle cx="150" cy="150" r="90" stroke="black" stroke-width="3"/>
            <path d="M80 80 L220 220" stroke="black" stroke-width="3"/>
            <path d="M220 80 L80 220" stroke="black" stroke-width="3"/>
            <circle cx="150" cy="150" r="30" stroke="black" stroke-width="3"/>
          </svg>
        </div>

        <div class="content-layer">
          <h1>Shadow Projection</h1>
          <p class="subtitle">dreams / projection / psyche / archive entry 005</p>

          <p>
            Shadow projection occurs when parts of the psyche that are not
            recognized are experienced as coming from outside. In dreams,
            this often appears as threatening figures, conflict, or strong
            emotional reactions.
          </p>

          <div class="quote">
            what is not seen within is often encountered as if it were outside.
          </div>

          <h2 class="section-title">projection</h2>
          <p>
            Instead of recognizing a quality internally, it is perceived in
            another figure. The dream then stages a confrontation with this
            disowned aspect.
          </p>

          <h2 class="section-title">recognition</h2>
          <p>
            The turning point comes when the figure is no longer seen as purely
            external, but as connected to the self.
          </p>

          <h2 class="section-title">integration</h2>
          <p>
            Bringing this material into awareness reduces reactivity and
            allows a more complete relationship to one’s own nature.
          </p>

          <div class="mini-links">
            <a class="blue" href="/dreams">back to dreams index</a>
            <a class="blue" href="/dreams/active-imagination">continue to: active imagination</a>
          </div>

          <p class="footer-note">this page is part of the hidden archive.</p>
        </div>
      </main>
    </div>
  </body>
</html>
